title: WATCH & VOTE: Doukara v Yeboah
text:
Get Sky Sports Get a Sky Sports pass 
"Such a special goal for me and the fans," Doukara posted on Twitter after his moment of glory. "Never see this shot again, thank u for coming, support always big." 
"It was a fantastic strike from Souleymane," said Monk after the game. "I don't think you'll see a cleaner or better strike this season." 
The Frenchman's effort echoed Yeboah's 1995 classic against Liverpool - a sensational arcing volley that crashed off the underside of the bar before crossing the line - but how does it compare? Souleymane Doukara came off the bench to steal the show for Leeds against Nottingham Forest 
Wowed by Doukara's precision or does the Ghanaian, who controlled the ball with chest and instep before his ferocious finish, still reign supreme? 
Watch both crackers in the video above then cast your vote... Also See:
